sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Admin
    participant API as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as NotebookReconciler<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    participant Culler as CullingReconciler<br/>Activity Monitor
    participant Browser as User Browser
    participant Gateway as Istio Ingress Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant VirtualSvc as VirtualService<br/>Routing Config
    participant NotebookSvc as Notebook Service<br/>80/TCP HTTP mTLS
    participant Pod as Notebook Pod<br/>8888/TCP HTTP Jupyter
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>Metrics Collector

    Note over User,Pod: Flow 1: Notebook Creation

    User->>API: kubectl create notebook<br/>OIDC/cert auth
    API->>Controller: Watch event<br/>Notebook CR created
    Controller->>API: Create StatefulSet<br/>ServiceAccount token
    API-->>Controller: StatefulSet created
    Controller->>API: Create Service<br/>Port 80→8888
    API-->>Controller: Service created
    Controller->>API: Create VirtualService<br/>(if USE_ISTIO=true)
    API-->>Controller: VirtualService created
    Controller->>API: Update Notebook status<br/>conditions: Running
    API->>Pod: Start Jupyter server<br/>via StatefulSet

    Note over Culler,Pod: Flow 2: Idle Notebook Culling

    Culler->>API: List all Notebooks<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+
    API-->>Culler: Notebook list
    Culler->>NotebookSvc: GET /api/kernels<br/>HTTP (mTLS if mesh)
    NotebookSvc->>Pod: Forward request<br/>HTTP 8888/TCP
    Pod-->>NotebookSvc: Kernel status JSON
    NotebookSvc-->>Culler: Activity data

    alt Notebook is idle > CULL_IDLE_TIME
        Culler->>API: Update Notebook annotation<br/>kubeflow-resource-stopped
        API->>Pod: Stop notebook pod
    end

    Note over Prom,Pod: Flow 3: Metrics Scraping

    Prom->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    Controller->>API: List StatefulSets<br/>HTTPS TLS1.2+
    API-->>Controller: StatefulSet data
    Controller-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics<br/>notebook_running, notebook_create_total

    Note over Browser,Pod: Flow 4: External User Access

    Browser->>Gateway: HTTPS /notebook/{ns}/{name}<br/>443/TCP TLS1.3 OAuth2/OIDC
    Gateway->>VirtualSvc: Route via config<br/>mTLS
    VirtualSvc->>NotebookSvc: Forward to notebook<br/>80/TCP HTTP mTLS
    NotebookSvc->>Pod: Forward to Jupyter<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    Pod-->>NotebookSvc: Jupyter UI response
    NotebookSvc-->>VirtualSvc: HTTP response
    VirtualSvc-->>Gateway: mTLS response
    Gateway-->>Browser: HTTPS response
